s**\\n\\nI’m finding that using an AggregationStrategy as a POJO feels more robust and aligns with supported behavior. The `AggregationStrategyBeanAdapter` can adapt any POJO method, so that seems useful, and UseLatest's aggregate is publicly accessible. The tests right now use test beans, which is fine, but I’m thinking it would be better to have the dynamic access metadata cover library classes instead of just the test classes. That way, it aligns more closely with the intended functionality.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_sXLZEAdgu0pTzsgCrHXyLdE1|fc_0b91d777a1a8e162016a2851aba7bc8197974ba233afc9c8b0", "name": "read", "arguments": {"path": "/home/jovan/Work/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/source_context/org.apache.camel/camel-core/2.16.2/main/extracted/org/apache/camel/processor/aggregate/UseOriginalAggregationStrategy.java", "limit": 120}, "partialJson": "{\"path\":\"/home/jovan/Work/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/source_context/org.apache.camel/camel-core/2.16.2/main/extracted/org/apache/camel/processor/aggregate/UseOriginalAggregationStrategy.java\",\"limit\":120}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1550, "output": 789, "cacheRead": 27136, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 29475, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1781027223748, "responseId": "resp_0b91d777a1a8e162016a28519865588197bd854ea0ef177dba"}}
